<!-- Game Description Table -->

<table class="tablestyle" id="table14" cellspacing="4" cellpadding="0">
	<tr>
		<td class="sectional">

<!-- Game Description Header -->
		
		<table class="headertable" id="table15" cellspacing="2" cellpadding="2">
			<tr>
				<td class="headercell">
				<img border="0" src="../../../images/headers/gamedes.jpg" width="240" height="33"></td>
			</tr>
		</table>

<!-- Game Description Sectional -->

<table border="0" width="100%" id="table16" cellpadding="0">
	<tr>
		<td style="font-family: Trebuchet MS; font-size: 8pt; color: #FFFFFF; font-weight: bold; text-align: left; background-color: #333333; border-left: 2px solid #000000; border-right: 2px solid #FFFFFF; border-top: 2px solid #000000; border-bottom: 2px solid #FFFFFF">
			<br>Enix serves a classically styled isometric console RPG with this release of Dragon Warrior VII. Players take the role of a youngster named Aluse who has grown up in a sleepy little fishing village on a small, remote island. Joined by his friends Maribel and Prince Kiefer, Aluse decides to explore the ancient and mysterious ruins outside of town and is led on an adventure that takes him across the island and through time itself.
                  <br><br>By confronting evil and solving puzzles, the adventurers can journey to the past and discover other islands and continents that existed near the island in earlier times. By solving quests in these ancient lands, the heroes can change the course of history so that the places come to exist in their own time as well.
                  <br><br>The story progresses in a linear fashion, as the main character discovers new lands, each with its own mysteries, characters, and adventures. The job system adds immense depth to character progression, as players can learn skills from more than 50 classes, including warriors, clerics, jesters, rangers, dragoons, teen idols, and more.
                  <br><br>Its creators include a trio of Japanese role-playing-game legends--game designer Yuji Horii, music composer Koichi Sugiyama, and character designer Akira Toriyama (who also created the popular Dragonball and Dragonball Z cartoons and comics)
                  <br><br>Features:
                  <br>* A fantasy-adventure game of epic proportions
                  <br>* Travel back in time and discover lost continents
                  <br>* Solve mysteries of the past to save the future
                  <br>* 3-D rendered backgrounds and fluid combat animation
                  <br>* An engrossing RPG experience true to the Dragon Warrior series
                  <br><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;<u>Manufacturer's description:</u><br>
                  <br>In the world, only this island is...
                  <br><br>You plan to become a humble fisherman of peaceful Estard Island, the only land in a world of ocean. But when you discover the artifacts from an ancient land, you tear the fabric of time and unveil the world that once was. Transported to past lands, you must solve their mysteries and break the spell of annihilation. Prepare for your destiny!
                  <br><br>Living, 3D worlds
                  <br>Latest in classic RPG series
                  <br>100s of Akira Toriyama monsters
                  <br><br>The Best Selling Japanese PlayStation game console Title of All Time!
                  <br><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;<u>Features:</u><br>
			<ul><li>Third person perspective.</li>
			<li>2D graphics</li>
			<li>Cartoon graphics</li>
			<li>Medieval Fantasy theme.</li></ul>
</td>

	</tr>
	</table>
	       	</td>
     </tr>
</table>  

